3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EI%20moved%20to%20Portland%2C%20Maine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20from%20Boston%20in%202003%20with%20my%20boyfriend%2C%20Craig%2C%20it%20was%20a%20pit%20stop%2C%20not%20a%20home.%20I%20had%20no%20desire%20to%20lay%20down%20roots.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20as%20far%20back%20as%20I%20could%20remember%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-to-los-angeles-to-make-it-and-failed-2020-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emy%20dream%20was%20to%20head%20out%20to%20Hollywood%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20make%20a%20name%20for%20myself%20in%20the%20film%20industry.%20I%20even%20attended%20graduate%20school%20and%20received%20an%20MA%20in%20television%2Fvideo%20production%20from%20Emerson%20College.%20At%20some%20point%20during%20our%20first%20date%2C%20Craig%20told%20me%20he%20wanted%20to%20become%20a%20comedy%20writer.%20Our%20plan%20was%20hatched.%20We%20were%20heading%20to%20Southern%20California.%20Of%20course%2C%20we%20would%20need%20time%20to%20save.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20decided%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsurprising-things-visiting-new-england-as-a-southerner-portland-maine-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Espend%20a%20year%20or%20so%20in%20Portland%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saving%20and%20preparing%20for%20the%20move%20out%20West.%20It's%20been%20over%2020%20years.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eb2124c9-79de-4021-83c8-4f7dec6da013%5C%22%3EOur%20families%20were%20in%20New%20England%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECraig%20was%20born%20and%20raised%20in%20Maine%2C%20and%20his%20parents%20still%20lived%20there.%20I%20was%20from%20a%20city%20north%20of%20Boston.%20While%20Craig's%20family%20originally%20came%20from%20Denmark%20and%20Ireland%2C%20and%20mine%20made%20their%20way%20over%20from%20Sicily%2C%20our%20ancestors%20decided%20to%20settle%20in%20New%20England.%20Our%20families%20were%20proud%20and%20devoted%20New%20Englanders%20for%20at%20least%20three%20generations.%20That%20tradition%20would%20end%20with%20us.%20As%20a%20kid%2C%20even%20before%20my%20California%20dreaming%2C%20I%20vowed%20I%20would%20never%20raise%20my%20children%20in%20New%20England.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-for-seasonal-depression-from-therapist-who-experiences-it-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EI%20hated%20the%20cold%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20didn't%20enjoy%20growing%20up%20in%20a%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20moved%20to%20Portland%20in%20August%202003%20from%20my%20small%20apartment%20in%20Massachusetts.%20I%20got%20rid%20of%20almost%20everything%20we%20owned%2C%20and%20we%20moved%20in%20with%20Craig's%20parents.%20Discovering%20he'd%20never%20let%20his%20parents%20know%20of%20our%20plan%20made%20my%20desire%20to%20leave%20even%20stronger.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20managed%20to%20find%20jobs%2C%20and%20we%20began%20to%20save.%20I%20promised%20myself%20I%20wouldn't%20become%20attached%20to%20anything%20or%20anyone.%20Craig's%20mother%20made%20that%20impossible.%20She%20became%20a%20friend%20and%20surrogate%20mother.%20Still%2C%20I%20planned.%20I%20spent%20evenings%20searching%20for%20apartments%20online%20and%20days%20stashing%20away%20the%20money%20I%20earned%20working%20at%20a%20daycare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2278f1e6a3-e7dd-4a21-927c-0a63d186a46e%5C%22%3EI%20got%20pregnant%20with%20our%20first%20kid%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20eight%20months%20after%20we%20moved%20to%20Maine%2C%20I%20had%20a%20strange%20feeling.%20I'd%20missed%20my%20period%20and%20was%20exhausted%20at%20the%20end%20of%20each%20day.%20A%20week%20later%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-take-a-pregnancy-test-2018-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etwo%20pink%20lines%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20me%20what%20I%20already%20believed%20was%20true.%20I%20was%20pregnant.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20tried%20to%20imagine%20moving%20to%20Los%20Angeles%20with%20a%20new%20baby%20and%20no%20support%20system.%20Who%20would%20we%20call%20in%20times%20of%20crisis%20or%20%3Ca%20