%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68cb136c183847aa39d6f833%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222362%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESam%20Altman%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20OpenAI%2C%20said%20Meta%20tried%20to%20recruit%20his%20employees%20by%20offering%20them%20%24100%20million%20signing%20bonuses.%3Cp%3EJakub%20Porzycki%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-full-stack-dream-microsoft-nightmare-2025-9%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20its%20AI%20models%20tend%20to%20scheme%20in%20various%20ways%2C%20which%20could%20cause%20harm%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EScheming%20is%20when%20AI%20breaks%20rules%20or%20pursues%20hidden%20agendas.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOpenAI%20says%20it%20has%20some%20ideas%20to%20fix%20the%20problem%20before%20it's%20too%20late.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESmarter%20AI%20doesn't%20always%20mean%20better%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-competition-big-tech-meta-talent-windsurf-amazon-movie-deepmind-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20new%20research%20this%20week%2C%20in%20conjunction%20with%20AI%20safety%20organization%20Apollo%20Research%2C%20that%20shows%20that%20its%20AI%20models%20are%20capable%20of%20%26quot%3Bscheming.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScheming%2C%20by%20the%20researchers'%20definition%2C%20is%20when%20AI%20pretends%20to%20be%20aligned%20with%20human%20goals%20but%20is%20surreptitiously%20pursuing%20another%20agenda.%20The%20researchers%20used%20behaviors%20like%20%26quot%3Bsecretly%20breaking%20rules%20or%20intentionally%20underperforming%20in%20tests%26quot%3B%20as%20examples%20of%20a%20model's%20bad%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20the%20company%20says%2C%20the%20stakes%20are%20still%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BModels%20have%20little%20opportunity%20to%20scheme%20in%20ways%20that%20could%20cause%20significant%20harm%2C%26quot%3B%20OpenAI%20said%20in%20a%20blog%20post%20on%20Wednesday.%20%26quot%3BThe%20most%20common%20failures%20involve%20simple%20forms%20of%20deception%20%E2%80%94%20for%20instance%2C%20pretending%20to%20have%20completed%20a%20task%20without%20actually%20doing%20so.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-openai-report-chatgpt-use-nber-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20it's%20better%20to%20take%20preventative%20action%20before%20AI%20becomes%20more%20sophisticated%20and%20its%20scheming%20could%20result%20in%20real-world%20harm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20says%20the%20solution%20is%20%26quot%3Bdeliberative%20alignment%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20training%20paradigm%20that%20OpenAI%20says%20it's%20been%20exploring.%20It%20forces%20large%20language%20models%20to%20reason%20explicitly%20about%20these%20safety%20specifications%20before%20answering%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20OpenAI%20told%20Business%20Insider%20by%20email%20that%20deliberative%20alignment%20means%20that%20instead%20of%20training%20a%20model%20to%20do%20one%20thing%20or%20another%2C%20it%20is%20taught%20the%20%26quot%3Bprinciples%20behind%20good%20behavior.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20blog%20post%2C%20OpenAI%20compared%20scheming%20to%20the%20behavior%20of%20a%20stock%20trader%20who%20breaks%20the%20law%20to%20earn%20more%20money%2C%20but%20is%20good%20at%20covering%20their%20tracks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStandard%20machine%20learning%20training%20would%20be%20like%20not%20telling%20the%20stock%20trader%20the%20rules%2C%20and%20just%20rewarding%20them%20for%20making%20money%20and%20punishing%20them%20for%20breaking%20rules%20until%20they%20figure%20out%20some%20way%20to%20behave%20that%20balances%20between%20the%20two%2C%26quot%3B%20OpenAI's%20spokesperson%20said.%20%26quot%3BDeliberative%20